[SN]TITLE[SN]
Blind man 'victim of firework hate crime' in Ammanford

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A blind man has been the victim of a hate crime attack after a firework was thrown at him and his guide dog, police have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It was lobbed from a moving car as the victim walked along Penybanc Road, Ammanford, Carmarthenshire, at about 11:30 GMT on Sunday, Dyfed-Powys Police said.
Officers tweeted for witnesses to come forward, calling the attack a hate crime.
Those with information should call 101.
